  <article id="section-confirmation-dialogs">
    <section class="">
      <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Confirmation Dialogs</h2>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Confirmation Dialogs require the user to confirm their choice before a selection is committed. For example, users can listen to possible notification sounds and then tap "Done" to confirm the choice and close the dialog.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Tapping "Cancel" cancels the action, discards any changes, and closes the dialog.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Avoid dialogs launching dialogs</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Confirmation dialogs should avoid launching additional simple dialogs as they add complexity and increase the elevation.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">If more steps are needed to complete the task, consider using full-screen dialogs instead.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/confirmation-dialog.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Confirmation dialog with option selected" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A confirmation dialog</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Stacked actions</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Confirmation button text should stay as concise as possible.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">If the button width needs to exceed the width available next to the dismissive button, the buttons may become stacked with the confirmation action above the dismissive action.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/stacked-actions-dialog.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="A confirmation dialog with stacked actions" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A confirmation dialog with stacked actions</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
  {{!-- / Confirmation DIALOGS article --}}

