  <article id="section-full-screen-dialogs">
    <section class="app-section">
      <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Full-screen Dialogs (Small screen only)</h2>

      <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
        <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: Due to limited space, full-screen dialogs may be more appropriate for mobile devices than dialogs used on devices with larger screens.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="row app-section">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Usage</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Full-screen dialogs group a series of tasks (such as creating a calendar entry) before they may be committed or discarded. No selections are saved until the affirmative action is touched. Touching "Close" discards all changes and exits the dialog.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Full-screen dialogs enable complex layouts and temporarily reset the app’s perceived elevation to a higher baseline. They allow tasks to launch menus or simple dialogs as part of a complex operation.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Full-screen dialogs may be used for content or tasks that meet any of these criteria:
              <ul class="app-list app-list--bulleted">
                <li class="app-list__item">The dialog includes components (like pickers or form fields) that require an input method editor (IME), such as a keyboard</li>
                <li class="app-list__item">When changes are not saved in real time</li>
                <li class="app-list__item">When there is no draft capability in the app</li>
                <li class="app-list__item">When performing batch operations or queuing changes prior to submitting them</li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/full-screen-dialog.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="A full-screen dialog dialog before input" />
                <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">A full-screen dialog dialog before input</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/full-screen-dialog-enabled.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="The confirmation action becomes enabled once all mandatory fields have been filled." />
                <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">The confirmation action becomes enabled once all mandatory fields have been filled.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row app-section">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Actions</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Place confirmation and dismissive actions for full-screen dialogs at the top of the screen.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Confirmation</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The confirmation action in the top right of the screen uses descriptive verbs, such as: save, add, send, share, update or create. Don’t use vague words for confirming action, such as: done, ok or close.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: The confirmation action should be disabled until all mandatory fields in the dialog are met.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Discard</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The discard action (the “Close” at the top left of the screen) closes the full-screen dialog and discards any changes.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Full-screen dialogs may be used for content or tasks that meet any of these criteria:
              <ul class="app-list app-list--bulleted">
                <li class="app-list__item">If no changes have been made, the dialog closes and no discard confirmation is required</li>
                <li class="app-list__item">If the user has made any changes, they are prompted to confirm the discard action</li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-1">
              <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--do">
                <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/full-screen-dialog-discard.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Prompt users to confirm the discard action if they have made any changes." />
                <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Prompt users to confirm the discard action if they have made any changes.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row app-section">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Titles</h3>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Full-screen dialog titles don’t use dynamic type.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Titles should be succinct. They can wrap to a second line if necessary, and should then be truncated.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">If the full-screen dialog uses titles of variable length or anticipates long titles (for example, because certain words are longer in different languages), place title text in the content area of the dialog instead of the app bar.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--dont">
                <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/variable-length-titles-dont.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Avoid using variable length titles in full screen dialogs." />
                <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Avoid using variable length titles in full-screen dialogs.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--do">
                <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/variable-length-titles-do.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Place long titles in the content area of a full-screen dialog and use a concise version of the title in the header." />
                <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Place long titles in the content area of a full-screen dialog and use a concise version of the title in the header.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
